+# ACP Pilot 57 — Protocol Findings
+
+## Metadata
+
+| Field | Value |
+|---|---|
+| **Pilot identifier** | `ACP-PILOT-57` |
+| **Date** | `2026-07-20` |
+| **Reviewed work** | `GH-57` — Audiobookshelf architecture review |
+| **ACP version used** | `0.1.0-draft` |
+| **Reviewer** | ChatGPT |
+| **Review result** | `PASS_WITH_FINDINGS` |
+
+## Summary
+
+Pilot 57 applied ACP `0.1.0-draft` to the Audiobookshelf architecture review
+(GH-57). The protocol specification was effectively empty (no normative
+content), so the review was conducted against the intent of ACP rather than
+its letter. The pilot produced 7 canonical findings about the protocol itself,
+directly informing which sections of ACP need to be drafted first.
+
+## Canonical Findings
+
+### F-57-001 — ACP
+
+| Field | Value |
+|---|---|
+| **Finding** | A mandatory transport validation step before `review_ready` was missing |
+| **Candidate for ACP revision** | **Yes** |
+
+### F-57-002 — ACP
+
+| Field | Value |
+|---|---|
+| **Finding** | Reviews require a deterministic review package structure instead of freely organized artifacts |
+| **Candidate for ACP revision** | **Yes** |
+
+### F-57-003 — ACP
+
+| Field | Value |
+|---|---|
+| **Finding** | Evidence should be explicitly mapped to Acceptance Criteria |
+| **Candidate for ACP revision** | **Yes** |
+
+### F-57-004 — Prompt
+
+| Field | Value |
+|---|---|
+| **Finding** | The implementation prompt did not sufficiently specify the review package |
+| **Candidate for ACP revision** | **No** |
+
+### F-57-005 — Reviewer
+
+| Field | Value |
+|---|---|
+| **Finding** | Multiple review iterations were required to separate transport defects from implementation defects |
+| **Candidate for ACP revision** | **No** |
+
+### F-57-006 — ACP
+
+| Field | Value |
+|---|---|
+| **Finding** | A dedicated review state for missing review artifacts would improve the protocol |
+| **Candidate for ACP revision** | **Yes** |
+
+### F-57-007 — Process
+
+| Field | Value |
+|---|---|
+| **Finding** | SHA-bound approvals proved effective and should be retained |
+| **Candidate for ACP revision** | **No** (retain as best practice) |
+
+## Summary
+
+Pilot 57 produced 7 canonical findings: 4 target the ACP specification itself
+(F-57-001, F-57-002, F-57-003, F-57-006), 1 targets the prompt engineering
+process (F-57-004), 1 targets the review workflow (F-57-005), and 1 confirms
+an existing practice (F-57-007). The findings with "Yes" for ACP revision
+directly inform which sections of the protocol need to be drafted first.
+
+## Recommendation
+
+**Candidate for future ACP revision?** `Yes`
+
+**Rationale:** Four of seven findings directly demand ACP changes:
+deterministic review package structure (F-57-002), evidence-to-AC mapping
+(F-57-003), mandatory transport validation (F-57-001), and a dedicated review
+state for missing artifacts (F-57-006). These should be addressed in the first
+normative ACP release.
+
