+# Findings
+
+This directory accumulates observations from ACP Pilots — structured reviews that
+apply the Agent Coordination Protocol to real PRs and issues.
+
+## Purpose
+
+Every ACP Pilot produces findings that fall into four categories:
+
+| Category | Scope |
+|---|---|
+| **ACP** | Deficiencies or gaps in the ACP specification itself |
+| **Prompt** | How well LLM prompts express ACP concepts |
+| **Reviewer** | How effective the reviewer applies ACP |
+| **Process** | Operational practices that should be retained or codified |
+
+These findings drive ACP revisions. Without findings, the protocol stagnates.
+
+## Workflow
+
+1. A Pilot is defined (issue, PR, scope, ACP version)
+2. The reviewer applies ACP and documents observations
+3. Findings are classified, prioritised, and merged via PR into this directory
+4. After review, findings may trigger ACP revision proposals in `DECISIONS/`
+
+## Register
+
+| Pilot | Date | Reviewed | ACP Version | Result | Document |
+|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|
+| 57 | 2026-07-20 | GH-57 (Audiobookshelf) | 0.1.0-draft | PASS_WITH_FINDINGS | PILOT-57.md |
+
+## Template
+
+Use `FINDINGS/TEMPLATE.md` when documenting a new Pilot. Each findings file uses
+the naming convention `PILOT-<NUMBER>.md`.
